üîóüß† Week-3 | Day-7 ‚Äì LangChain Architecture & Workflows

This document explains how **LangChain** is structured internally and how workflows are built using its components in **Agentic AI systems**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìå 1. Why Understand LangChain Architecture?

Understanding architecture helps you:

* Design scalable AI systems
* Avoid messy pipelines
* Build multi-step workflows
* Prepare for interviews
* Move from beginner ‚Üí AI engineer mindset

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© 2. High-Level LangChain Architecture

```text
User Input
   ‚Üì
Prompt Template
   ‚Üì
LLM
   ‚Üì
Memory (Optional)
   ‚Üì
Tools (Optional)
   ‚Üì
Output
```

LangChain acts as a **coordinator** between:

* LLMs
* Prompts
* Memory
* Tools
* Chains
* Agents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìå 3. Core Architectural Layers

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.1 Model Layer (LLM Layer)

Responsible for:

* Text generation
* Reasoning
* Decision making

Supports:

* OpenAI
* Hugging Face
* Ollama
* Local models

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.2 Prompt Layer

Handles:

* Structured prompts
* Dynamic variable insertion
* Template reuse

Example:

```text
"Explain {topic} in simple terms."
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.3 Chain Layer

Chains connect multiple components.

Example:

```text
Input ‚Üí Prompt ‚Üí LLM ‚Üí Output
```

Types:

* LLMChain
* SequentialChain
* SimpleChain

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.4 Memory Layer

Adds context persistence.

Types:

* ConversationBufferMemory
* ConversationSummaryMemory
* VectorStoreRetrieverMemory

Used in:

* Chatbots
* Multi-step agents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.5 Tool Layer

Allows LLM to:

* Search web
* Query database
* Run Python code
* Access files

Tools are invoked when:

* The agent decides it needs external info

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 3.6 Agent Layer

Agents:

* Decide which tool to use
* Plan actions
* Execute multi-step reasoning

This is the **core of Agentic AI in LangChain**.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÅ 4. LangChain Workflow Types

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 4.1 Simple LLM Workflow

```text
User ‚Üí Prompt ‚Üí LLM ‚Üí Response
```

Use Case:

* Basic Q&A

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 4.2 RAG Workflow

```text
User Query
   ‚Üì
Retriever (Vector DB)
   ‚Üì
Context
   ‚Üì
LLM
   ‚Üì
Final Answer
```

Use Case:

* Document-based chatbot

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 4.3 Tool-Based Agent Workflow

```text
User Query
   ‚Üì
Agent (LLM Reasoning)
   ‚Üì
Tool Selection
   ‚Üì
Tool Execution
   ‚Üì
Observation
   ‚Üì
Final Answer
```

Use Case:

* Research assistant
* Automation agent

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîπ 4.4 Multi-Step Sequential Workflow

```text
Step 1 ‚Üí Step 2 ‚Üí Step 3 ‚Üí Final Output
```

Use Case:

* Report generation
* Data analysis pipelines

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìå 5. LangChain Architecture vs Raw LLM API

| Feature          | Raw LLM | LangChain  |
| ---------------- | ------- | ---------- |
| Prompt Handling  | Manual  | Structured |
| Multi-step Logic | Hard    | Easy       |
| Tool Integration | Custom  | Built-in   |
| Memory           | Manual  | Built-in   |
| Scalability      | Low     | High       |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìå 6. How LangChain Fits in Agentic AI

LangChain enables:

* Tool-using agents
* Memory-aware agents
* RAG systems
* Multi-agent workflows
* Scalable AI pipelines

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ö†Ô∏è Common Beginner Mistakes

* Using chains when agent is required
* Overusing memory
* Not controlling tool permissions
* Ignoring token limits

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üéØ Key Takeaways

* LangChain organizes LLM apps into layers
* Chains handle sequences
* Agents handle decision-making
* Memory improves context
* Tools enable real-world interaction

Understanding this makes you capable of designing **production-level Agentic AI systems** üî•

